threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an IRC-based DDoS bot, likely a variant of the Kaiten family, targeting MIPS-based Linux devices. It connects to an IRC server to receive commands. Its primary malicious behaviors include launching various DDoS attacks (DNS, ICMP Blacknurse, UDP/TCP floods), backdoor functionality to download and execute arbitrary files and commands, and establishing persistence by modifying startup scripts like `/etc/rc.d/rc.local`. Notable IOCs include the command-and-control (C2) related URL `http://pirati[.]abuser[.]eu/yak.sh;` for downloading additional payloads and shell commands like `cd /root;rm -f .bash_history` to clear its tracks.
